🔑 DSA Pattern / Concept
- Pattern: Greedy (sum of all positive differences)  
- Why?  
  - You can buy and sell multiple times, but only hold one unit at a time.  
  - The optimal strategy is to capture every upward slope:  
    \[
    \text{profit} = \sum_{i=1}^{n-1} \max(0, colors[i] - colors[i-1])
    \]  
  - This works because you can buy at every valley and sell at every peak.

---

📌 Function Signature (LeetCode style)
`cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& colors) {
        int profit = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < colors.size(); i++) {
            if (colors[i] > colors[i-1]) {
                profit += colors[i] - colors[i-1];
            }
        }
        return profit;
    }
};
`

